ttention recently. Since the principle has been dealt with very differently across disciplines, the aim of the two volumes is to bring together the diverging approaches. They assemble a collection of original papers that cover the topic of compositionality from virtually all perspectives of interest in the contemporary debate. The well-chosen international list of authors includes psychologists, neuroscientists, computer scientists, linguists, and philosophers.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCognition. 0aCompositionality (Linguistics). 0aMeaning (Philosophy). 4aLinguistik. 4aPhilosophie. 4aSemantik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Logic.2bisacsh1 aCohnitz, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElugardo, Reinaldo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFernando, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGemes, Ken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGottschling, Verena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacob, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeitgeb, Hannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLievers, Menno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMachery, Edouard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMari, Alda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMateu, Jaume, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeregrin, Jaroslav, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPietarinen, Ahti-Veikko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchurz, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/re